name: Ah-Tah-Thi-Ki Museum
description: The museum has more than 180,000 artifacts that will help you learn about the culture and history of the Seminole Indians.
address: Big Cypress Seminole Reservation, 34725 W Boundary Rd, Clewiston, FL 33440

name: Air Force Armament Museum
description: Displays of armament of aviation warfare from World War One all the way to today's high tech planes, guns, and bombs. Admission Free.

name: Air Force Space & Missile Museum
description: The museum opened in 1966 and includes many exhibits about the history of rocketry and space flight.
address: Launch Complex 26, Kennedy Space Center, Kennedy Space Center Visitor Complex

name: AJ's Water Adventures
description: Many ways to enjoy the clear emerald waters including sailing on a 74 foot schooner and blasting along on a 53 foot speedboat. Fees vary by adventure.

name: Albin Polasek Museum and Sculpture Gardens
description: Home and studio of a prominent American sculptor. Included are several of his major works and a beautiful sculpture garden.

name: Alexander Springs Recreational Area
description: The recreation area offers camping, swimming, canoeing, scuba diving, hiking, birding and wildlife viewing. It is among 27 first-magnitude springs in Florida and is one of the easiest for visitors to enjoy.

name: Amelia Island Horseback Riding
description: You call Debbie Manser who meets you at the park with horses you can ride on the Atlantic Ocean beach. Fees vary by selected ride and number of people.
address: Peters Point Rd, Amelia Island, FL 32034

name: Appleton Museum of Art
description: A stunning example of classical architecture clad in Italian travertine marble. The 81,610-square-foot museum features 30,000 square feet of gallery space devoted to the Appleton's permanent collections.
address: College of Central Florida, 4333 E Silver Springs Blvd, Ocala, FL 34470

name: Asolo Repertory Theater
description: This theater is an important part of Sarasota's arts scene. It stages up to fifteen productions every season, ranging from new plays to reinterpretations of classical and contemporary works.

name: Babcock Ranch Eco Tours
description: The tours take place on a 92,000 acre working ranch where you will see not only wildlife but typical cattle ranching operations.

name: Bahia Honda State Park
description: Great view of the ocean, a nice beach, swimming, boating, fishing, and snorkeling.
address: 36850 Overseas Hwy, Big Pine Key, FL 33043

name: Bailey-Matthew National Shell Museum
description: This museum is a reference center for scientists and amateur shell collectors. Shells from all over the world are on display.

name: Barnacle Historic State Park
description: This was the home of Coconut Grove pioneer Ralph Middleton Munroe, who preserved the natural areas around his home. Today's park looks like the homestead did in 1891.

name: Big Cypress National Preserve
description: 720,000 acre preserve established in 1974.
address: Big Cypress Swamp Welcome Center, 3300 Tamiami Trail East, Ochopee, Florida 34141

name: Billy Swamp Safari
description: Tours and attractions including swamp buggy tours through the natural settings of the Everglades. See a Seminole snake show. Admission fee varies.

name: Biltmore Hotel
description: A magnificent structure built in 1926 and was at that time the tallest building in Florida at 315 feet. You can eat and sleep and gawk. It's free to just walk in and look.

name: Biscayne National Park
description: The park is nearly 173,000 acres and most of it is underwater. You will enjoy yourself in this park. You can snorkel, camp, boat, watch wildlife, fish, take guided eco-adventures, or just relax.
address: 9700 Southwest 328th Street, Sir Lancelot Jones Way, Homestead, Florida 33033

name: Blowing Rocks Preserve
description: You will enjoy the amazing breaking waves at this environmental preserve on Jupiter Island. When the surf is heavy, the waves force themselves through holes in the limestone and can blow ocean spray as high as 50 feet in the air. It's free.
address: 574 S Beach Rd, Hobe Sound, FL 33455

name: Blue Spring State Park
description: This park is a tremendous spot to observe manatees sheltering from the cold in the clear waters from November to March.
address: 2100 West French Ave., Orange City, FL 32763

name: Bob's River Place
description: A rustic attraction on the Suwannee River with water slides, rope swings, docks, waterwheels, ladders: an old fashioned swimming hole. Admission fee varies.

name: Boggy Creek Airboat Adventures
description: This fleet of 12 airboats takes you on a wide variety of tours where you will see wildlife including water birds and alligators. Admission fee varies.

name: Bok Tower Gardens
description: The tower and gardens are a historic setting on one of the highest hills in Florida. Enjoy daily carillon concerts.

name: Bonnet House Museum and Gardens
description: A 35 acre estate with a main house full of art and grounds that have some of the last remaining Florida beach native habitat.
address: 900 North Birch Rd, Fort Lauderdale, FL 33304

name: Boutique Adventures LLC
description: A tour company that takes small groups to central Florida off the beaten path places.

name: Breakers Hotel
description: It was opened in 1886 by Henry Flagler. On the ocean and a great place to tour, dine, eat, and stay. It's free to walk in and look.
address: One South County Rd, Palm Beach, FL 33480

name: Brevard Zoo
description: This popular zoo was built entirely by volunteers and has award winning interactive exhibits, many designed to please children.

name: Broward Center for the Performing Arts
description: It is ranked in the top ten most visited theaters in the world. More than 700,000 patrons enjoy more than 700 performances each year.

name: Busch Gardens
description: This is a 335 acre animal themed park with 8 roller coasters, 3 water rides, and many other rides and animal attractions. Admission fee varies.

name: Butterfly World
description: Located in Tradewinds Park, the largest butterfly park in the world with more than 20,000 live butterflies an a hummingbird aviary.
address: 3600 West Sample Rd, Coconut Creek, FL

name: Ca'da'Zan, Ringling Home
description: The home of John Ringling, the circus tycoon. Now a museum and location for interesting art and circus memorabilia tours.

name: Cassadaga-Mediums and Healers
description: This small village was established in 1895 by a spiritualist organization and is home to many mediums, psychics, and healers.

name: Castillo de San Marcos
description: The oldest 17th century fort in North America, this well preserved fort dominates the waterfront in downtown St. Augustine. There are many exhibits and guided and self guided tours.
address: 1 South Castillo Dr, St Augustine, FL 32084

name: Cat Boat Adventures
description: You will pilot your own twin hulled motor boat on Lake Dora while a captain in his own boat narrates and points out highlights.
address: Mount Dora Boating Center & Marina, 148 Charles Avenue, Mount Dora, FL 32757

name: Catty Shack Ranch Wildlife Sanctuary
description: A non-profit sanctuary that gives big cats a permanent home. They have lions, tigers, pumas, leopards, lynxes and more.

name: Central Florida Railroad Museum
description: This is a small museum is managed by the Central Florida Railway Historical Society, Inc. It focuses on the railroads of Central Florida.
address: 101 S Boyd St, Winter Garden, FL 34787

name: Chinsegut Hill Retreat
description: Historic plantation home on one of the highest hills in Central Florida. Serves mainly as conference retreat and wedding venue.

name: Clyde Butcher's Big Cypress Gallery
description: A large collection of the photographer's work.

name: Coral Castle
description: A lovesick immigrant from Lithuania spent most of his life building this monument to the sweetheart who jilted him at the altar.

name: Corkscrew Swamp Sanctuary
description: This sanctuary has preserved the last remaining large stands of bald cypress and pond cypress in North America.

name: Cracker Country Rural History Museum
description: This living history museum is open to the public during the Florida State Fair in February.

name: Cummer Museum of Art and Gardens
description: The Cummer has one of the finest permanent art collections in Florida, with nearly 5,000 objects. This art ranges in age from 2100 B.C. through modern times.

name: Dade Battlefield Historic State Park
description: This park was established in 1921 to preserve and commemorate the site of Dade's Battle of 1835. Of 110 American soldiers, only 3 survived the ambush by Seminoles. It precipitated am awful war.

name: Dali Museum
description: This museum displays the work of only one artist, Salvador Dali. It is home to an amazing collection of traditional and modern art.

name: Daytona International Speedway
description: If you visit during other than the featured events, such as the historic Daytona 500, you can go on a first come-first served tour.
address: 1801 West International Speedway Blvd, Daytona Beach, FL 32114

name: DeFuniak Springs Historic District
description: A large collection of functioning Victorian homes and buildings. It is may have more such buildings than any other town in the U.S.
address: City of DeFuniak Springs71 US 90 West, DeFuniak Springs, FL 32433

name: Deseret Ranches
description: This is one of the largest working cow-calf ranches in the United States. It's 295,000 acres sprawl between Orlando and Cocoa. Tours are available.
address: Visitor and Information Center, 3584 Orchid Circle, St Cloud, Florida 34773

name: Devil's Millhopper Geological State Park
description: You walk down a 232-step wooden staircase into the bottom of a geological formation that has been attracting visitors for well over a century.

name: Dinosaur World
description: The entire family will love wandering around this place that features replicas of more than 150 dinosaurs. It's fun and educational.
address: 5145 Harvey Tew Road, Plant City, FL 33565

name: Disney Springs
description: Spend a day to two and this giant outdoor shopping, dining, and entertainment complex at Walt Disney World.

name: Don Garlits Museum of Drag Racing
description: This museum has more than 90 race cars on display and another 50 antique cars. Garlits is a former champion drag racer.

name: Dr. Phillips Center for the Performing Arts
description: The 2-block Center includes the Walt Disney Theater, the Alexis & Jim Pugh Theater, the DeVos Family Room, the Seneff Arts Plaza, and many other spaces set aside for private events.

name: Dry Tortugas National Park
description: You can take a long day trip or enjoy a camping adventure by visiting Dry Tortugas National Park about 70 miles west of Key West. It is home to Fort Jefferson.
address: Mailing Address: 40001 State Road 9556, Homestead, FL 33034

name: Edison and Ford Winter Estates
description: The great inventor and his auto tycoon friend had winter homes side by side on the Caloosahatchee River. You can visit these amazing places and see where Edison worked on his inventions.

name: Epcot
description: One of 4 theme parks at WDW, this is a park that celebrates human achievement in technology and culture.
address: Walt Disney World Resort, 200 Epcot Center Dr, Orlando, FL 32821

name: Everglades and Keys Kayak Tours
description: Run by Florida Bay Outfitters, this is where you can begin a wide variety of Florida Keys and South Florida paddling trips.

name: Everglades Rod and Gun Club
description: Rambling historic hotel on the Barron River.

name: Fairchild Tropical Botanic Garden
description: This 83 acre garden is one of the world's best tropical botanic gardens. It has the largest palm collection in the world.
address: 10901 Old Cutler Rd, Coral Gables, FL 33156

name: Fantasy of Flight
description: A display of more than 140 civilian and military planes and many of them can fly. Tours and learning about aviation history.
address: 1400 Broadway Blvd SE, Polk City, FL 33868

name: Farm Tours of Ocala
description: This is a 3 hours and 15 minute tour of working farms where you can go behind the scenes and chat with pros who work with thoroughbred horses.

name: Flagler College (Ponce de Leon Hotel)
description: The hotel was built by railroad tycoon Henry Flagler in 1888 and is a National Historic Landmark.You can take a tour and explore.

name: Flagler Museum, Whitehall
description: The former mansion of railroad tycooon Henry flagler, it is now a 73 room museum with guided tours, exhibits, and programs.
address: One Whitehall Way, Palm Beach, FL 33480

name: Florida Air Museum
description: This museum is designated as Florida's Official Aviation Museum and Education Center. It is housed in a building on the campus of the Sunn Fun fly-in and expo at Lakeland Linder International Airport.

name: Florida Aquarium
description: It is ranked in the top 10 U.S. aquariums by TripAdvisor. It focuses on teaching visitors about the ecosystems of Florida and the world.

name: Florida Caverns State Park
description: It is your chance to explore a network of underground caves created from limestone formations that have slowly dissolved over thousands of years.

name: Florida Citrus Tower
description: Built in 1956 during the glory days of citrus, this tall observation tower takes you up in an elevator where you can see the view.

name: Florida Keys Eco-Discovery Center
description: The center teaches you about the native plants, animals, and ecosystems of the Florida Keys. There are several exhibits including an interactive satellite map of the Florida Keys.
address: 35 East Quay Road, Key West, FL 33040

name: Florida Museum of Natural History
description: This free museum has one of the largest collections of natural history items in the U.S. Kids love the 14 foot tall mammoth skeleton.
address: University of Florida Cultural Plaza, SW 34th Street and Hull Road, PO Box 112710, Gainesville, FL 32611

name: Florida Railroad Museum
description: This is one of 3 official state railroad museums in Florida. The museum has a large collection of rolling stock including 9 locomotives and 15 cars including Pullmans, cabooses, and various kinds of freight cars.

name: Florida State Capitol
description: The old capitol building has been preserved and restored and is next door to the modern tower that serves as the headquarters for Florida's state government.
address: Florida's Capitol Complex, 400 South Monroe Street, Tallahassee, Florida 32399

name: Florida Theatre
description: First opened in 1927. In addition to 200 cultural and entertainment events each year including ballet, opera, pop, jazz, rock, country, blues, plays, and movies, it is also home to school graduations and charity events.

name: Fort Caroline National Memorial
description: This free attraction is on the south bank of the St. Johns River. It memorializes France's shore lived presence in Florida in the 16th century.

name: Fort Christmas Historical Park
description: The fort is a full-scale replica of the one that was built on Christmas Day, 1837. Many interesting buildings and artifacts.

name: Fort Clinch State Park
description: The park has 1,400 acres of natural beauty and a historic fort that sometimes has rangers dressed in period military uniforms.

name: Fort Desoto Park
description: 1,136 acres on 5 interconnected islands with great camping and beaches.

name: Fort Gates Ferry
description: Cars, motorcycles, or bikes can take this small ferry across the St. Johns River from the Ocala National Forest or a fish camp.
address: 229 Fort Gates Ferry Rd, Crescent City, FL 32112

name: Frank Lloyd Wright Child of the Sun
description: Home to several buildings designed by Frank Lloyd Wright. This collection is named Child of the Sun. All the structures are on the National Register of Historic Places and are working buildings used by students and faculty.
address: Florida Southern College, 111 Lake Hollingsworth Drive, Lakeland, FL 33801

name: Fruit And Spice Park
description: A county park devoted to fruits and spices. Things grow in this part of Florida that won't grow elsewhere in Florida or the United States.

name: Fun Spot America
description: On International Drive in Orlando, this has 4 different go-kart tracks and 3 roller coasters, plus another 3 different thrill rides.

name: Gatorland
description: One of Florida's oldest attractions, it still entertains with thousands of alligators and a thrilling canopy ride.
address: 14501 South Orange Blossom Trail, Orlando, FL 32837

name: Ginnie Springs Outdoors
description: This is a great place to camp or just chill out in the cool spring waters swimming, snorkeling, or kayaking.
address: 7300 Northeast Ginnie Springs Road, High Springs, FL 32643

name: Gulfarium Marine Adventure Park
description: Focuses on animal encounters with dolphins, stingrays, gators, reptiles, turtles, penguins, seals, and birds.
address: 1010 Miracle Strip Parkway SE, Fort Walton Beach, FL 32548

name: Gumbo Limbo Nature Center
description: Twenty acres of protected barrier island with ecosytems, exotic trees, and a turtle rehabilitation facility.
address: 1801 N Ocean Blvd, Boca Raton, FL 33432

name: Harbor Branch Ocean Discovery Center
description: When you step through the doors here, you will be entering a large functioning oceanographic research institution with a storied history.
address: 5600 N US Highway 1, Fort Pierce, FL 34946

name: Hemingway Home
description: The great author lived here from 1931 to 1940. It has many of his furnishings and the first in ground swimming pool in Key West.

name: Highlands Hammock State Park
description: This park has one of Florida's diverse collections of plant and animal life in Florida. The park is home to 1,000-year-old oaks, old growth hammock, and the Florida panther.

name: Ichetucknee Inner Tube Trip
description: A Florida tradition for years, floating down the clear cool river.
address: Ichetucknee Springs State Park12087 SW SR 27, Fort White, FL 32038

name: ICON Orlando
description: A giant 400 foot tall observation tower in the form of a Ferris Wheel with separate enclosed air conditioned observation capsules.

name: Jacksonville Museum of Science and History
description: Interactive exhibits about your body's systems , energy exhibits, and animal encounters. Also a boat tour on the St. Johns River.

name: Jacksonville Zoo
description: This historic zoo is organized around several major exhibits. You will see dozens of exotic birds, crocodiles, antelopes, cheetahs, zebras, elephants, lions, monkeys, and you can feed a sting ray.

name: Judah P. Benjamin Confederate Memorial
description: The memorial is a pre-Civil War mansion, the only surviving plantation house in south Florida.
address: Gamble Plantation State Park3708 Patten Ave, Ellenton, FL 34222

name: John Gorrie State Museum
description: Dr. Gorrie is considered the father of modern air conditioning. This museum has exhibits of his early experiments and Apalachicola memorabilia.

name: Jungle Island
description: Famous place where birds fly around without cages. It has more than 2,000 varieties of tropical plants and 1,100 tropical birds.

name: Jungle Queen Riverboat
description: You can enjoy day tours of the Fort Lauderdale waterways and also go on dinner cruises past the homes of the rich and famous.

name: Kayaking at Topsail Hill Preserve State Park
description: Visitors can kayak, canoe, or paddleboard on a coastal dune lake in this beautiful state park with beach dunes more than 25 feet high.

name: Kennedy Space Center Visitors Complex
description: This attraction will take all of a day and maybe two. You can plan your trip in advance and see hundreds of exhibits and displays, the real Space Shuttles, theaters, bus tours, and much more. Daily presentations for a veteran astronaut.

name: Key West Aquarium
description: This historic museum is a place where you can get up close and personal with animals such as horseshoe crabs and Florida lobster. You will enjoy a 90 minute guided tour.
address: 1 Whitehead Street (Mallory Square), Key West, Florida 33040

name: Key West Express
description: This two vessel passenger ferry operates between Fort Myers Beach, Marco Island, and Key West. It is a fast and comfortable way to travel.

name: Kingsley Plantation
description: Located on Fort George Island are the owner's house built about 1798 and the remains of 25 slave cabins.

name: Koreshan State Park
description: The buildings are preserved of a cult that believed the entire universe existed inside of a giant, hollow sphere. Interesting exhibits and a serene campground.

name: Lake Placid Murals
description: Downtown Lake Placid has one of the largest outdoor art displays in Florida. These displays are in the form of murals on building walls that celebrate the history of the area. At last count, there are 47 historic murals in town.
address: 18 North Oak St, Lake Placid, FL 33852

name: Legoland Florida Resort
description: Kids can assemble Lego toys on this 150 acre theme park with more than 50 rides, dozens of shows, shops, restaurants, and a water park.

name: Leu Gardens
description: The former estate of an Orlando businessman, this 50 acre botanical garden is divided into more than a dozen specialty gardens.

name: Lion Country Safari
description: You will love driving through this large attraction in your car while the animals roam free. You will see more than 1,000 exotic animals in something close to their natural habitat.
address: 2003 Lion Country Safari Road, Loxahatchee, FL 33470

name: Little Talbot Island State Park
description: Great camping and beach access.

name: Mallory Square
description: This is the gathering place for locals and visitors. There is all kind of entertainment, food vendors, and the best sunset in Florida. Free.

name: Marie Selby Botanical Gardens
description: This 15 acre garden is the only one in the world devoted to epiphytes. These include orchids, bromeliads, and hundreds of other plants.

name: Marineland Florida
description: Here you can swim with the dolphins. It is a dolphin research center that was once Florida's most popular tourist attraction.

name: Marjorie Kinnan Rawlings Historic State Park
description: You will experience what 1930s farm life was like when the famous author lived and worked here. Her Florida Cracker style home and farm has been restored and is preserved.

name: McLarty Treasure Museum
description: The museum is part of Sebastian Inlet State Park. It features treasure artificats and displays from some of the 11 Spanish galleons sunk in the ocean near here over 300 years ago.
address: 13180 N Hwy A1A, Vero Beach, FL 32963

name: Menello Museum of American Art
description: The museum's mission is to preserve, display, and interpret the permanent collection of paintings by Earl Cunningham, a folk artist who painted mostly coastal landscapes of America's Atlantic Coast.

name: Merritt Island National Wildlife Refuge
description: This huge refuge is in the shadow of Kennedy Space Center. It has 140,000 acres and over 1,000 species of plants, 117 fish species, and much more. It has miles of hiking and driving trails.

name: Miami Seaquarium
description: A 38 acre child friendly attraction where you can interact with dolphins, sea lions, sharks, birds, fish, and more.

name: Miccosukee Resort and Gaming
description: Gambling, entertainment, and tours.

name: Mill Creek Farm Retirement Home For Horses
description: Old horses wear out just like people. These horses used to pull carriages, support police forces, and just work. Here they can spend their senior years on a nice rolling horse farm. Admission fee 2 carrots.

name: Morikami Museum and Japanese Gardens
description: Japanese farmers established a colony in this area years ago. The museum celebrates their culture, has beautiful landscaped grounds, and a collection of bonsai trees.
address: 4000 Morikami Park Road, Delray Beach, Florida 33446

name: Morse Museum
description: The Charles Hosmer Morse Museum of American Art is home to the world's most comprehensive collection of the works of Louis Comfort Tiffany, including jewelry, pottery, paintings, art glass and more.
address: 445 N Park Ave, Winter Park, FL 32789

name: Mote Marine Laboratory and Aquarium
description: An independent research institution that studies manatees, dolphins, sea turtles, sharks, and coral reefs.

name: Murder Mystery Dinner Train
description: Have you ever wanted to go to a murder mystery dinner? Have you ever wanted to ride on a train? Here is your chance to do both.
address: Colonial Passenger Station, 2805 Colonial Blvd , Fort Myers, FL 33966

name: Museum of Florida History
description: The official history museum of the state focuses on artifacts and eras unique to Florida and roles Floridians have played in history. Free.

name: Museum of the Everglades
description: This small museum is in the former laundry building of the historic Everglades Rod and Gun Club. The building is on the National Register of Historic Places and has a small collection of artifacts.
address: 105 Broadway Ave West, Everglades City, FL 34139

name: Naples Botanical Garden
description: This unique garden specializes in plants that exist between 26 Latitude North and 26 Latitude South. They have plants from all over the world, and a 90 acre nature preserve with otters, eagles, and more.

name: Naples Princess Cruises
description: A 105 foot luxury yacht that offers daily public cruises along the waterfront in Naples. You will see magnificient homes, and can enjoy a sunset.
address: 550 Port O Call Way, Naples, FL 34102

name: Naples Zoo at Caribbean Gardens
description: One of the oldest zoos in Southwest Florida, it is divided into habitat areas where you can see animals in natural conditions.

name: National Naval Aviation Museum
description: Pensacola is the birthplace of naval aviation, and this museum has a superb large collection of navy aircraft and memorabilia. Admission Free.
address: 1750 Radford Blvd., Suite C, Naval Air Station Pensacola, FL 32508

name: National Navy UDT-SEAL Museum
description: Artifacts and exhibits dedicated to SEAL warriors and their predecessors, the Underwater Demolition Teams (UDT).
address: 3300 N Hwy A1A, Fort Pierce, FL 34949

name: Ocala National Forest
description: The forest has 607 square miles with 600 lakes, campgrounds, hiking and off road trails, and many animals including black bears, deer, boar, otters, and more. Admission free.
address: Lake George Ranger District, 17147 E SR 40, Silver Springs, Florida 34488

name: Ocean Drive Art Deco District
description: South Beach has an interesting mix of well preserved and functioning hotels, restaurants, and shops with Art Deco, Mediterranean Revival, and Miami Modern Styles.

name: Oldest House Museum Complex
description: The Oldest House Museum Complex is located across from the historic National Guard building in downtown St. Augustine.

name: Olustee Battlefield Historic State Park
description: A site of a significant Civil War battle. U.S. Colored troops took part in the battle. You can see exhibits and artifacts in the visitor center.

name: Orange County Regional History Center.
description: This museum celebrates Central Florida history all the way from the first Native Americans to today's giant theme parks.

name: Orlando Science Center
description: It teaches science and makes sure kids have fun doing it. A large facility with 4 floors of science exhibits, giant screen movie theaters, and live programming, exhibit halls and science stations.

name: Paynes Prairie Preserve State Park
description: A 22,000 acre savannah with a wide variety of wildlife including bison and horses in addition to hundreds of bird varieties.

name: Pensacola Historic Village
description: Historic Pensacola is a neighborhood of 28 historic buildings and museums. Charming homes, shops, restaurants, and galleries.

name: Philharmonic Center for the Arts
description: Fondly called "The Phil" by locals, the Philharmonic complex in Naples includes the Baker Museum as well as the performing home of the Naples Philharmonic Orchestra.

name: Ponce de Leon Inlet Lighthouse
description: The lighthouse is on an inlet south of Daytona Beach. You can climb to the top and see a fantastic view of the ocean and beaches.
address: 4931 South Peninsula Dr., Ponce Inlet, FL 32127

name: Rainbow Springs State Park
description: At the park's main entrance you can swim in the freshwater Rainbow River, rent canoes and kayaks, view waterfalls and gardens and enjoy a picnic area with grills, and pavilions.

name: Raymond E. Kravis Center for the Performing Arts
description: The center has a performance and black box theater, an amphitheater and an events hall. It is the first performing arts center in the world to have a custom-designed digital organ.
address: 701 Okeechobee Blvd, West Palm Beach, FL 33401

name: Renninger's Mount Dora Twin Markets
description: This is a huge antique center and adjacent flea market on the same property. Each market has hundreds of vendors. Antiques, clothing, plants, product, eggs, meat, pets, and about anything else.

name: Richloam General Store
description: The store is a historic structure dating back to 1922 that was originally used as a general store. Over the years it also served as a railroad express station and post office. Today it is a gift shop and museum and a glimpse into of Old Florida.
address: 38219 Richloam Clay Sink Road, Webster, FL

name: Ringling Museum of Art
description: The John and Mable  is the official art museum for the State of Florida. The huge museum contains 21 galleries of European paintings as well as many pieces of Asian, American, and contemporary art.

name: Ripley's Believe It Or Not! Museum
description: The bizarre objects here include 20,000 photographs, 3,000 artifacts, and more than 100 panels from Ripley's cartoons.
address: 19 San Marco Ave, St Augustine, FL 32084

name: River Safaris
description: They have airboat tours, rental boats, pontoon boat tours, manatee tours, scalloping and fishing adventures and more.

name: Robert Is Here
description: One of the largest produce stands in Florida, it features an amazing selection of tropical fruits grown in South Florida.

name: Robert The Doll
description: Robert is a spooky doll on display here that many people believe is haunted.
address: Fort East Martello Museum, Key West, FL 33040

name: Sarasota Jungle Gardens
description: A 10 acre tropical site with more than 200 animals including birds of prey, parrots, macaws, primates, small mammals, snakes, lizards and more. There is a large flock of pink flamingos that are friendly.

name: Scalloping in the Gulf of Mexico
description: Scalloping season is usually July through September. During season, thousands of people gather along the gulf coast from south of Steinhatchee up to the Carrabelle area. Their fishing equipment consists of snorkel gear and buckets.
address: Florida Fish and Wildlife Conservation Commission, 620 South Meridian St, Tallahassee, FL 32399

name: Schooner Freedom
description: This is a 76 foot schooner where you can go for a sail and even help sail it. You will see the sights of the Ancient City.

name: Seacrest Wolf Preserve
description: The preserve offers visitors a walking rip into natural habitat where they will see Gray, Arctic, and British Columbian wolves.

name: Seaworld Orlando
description: Three different parks in one: SeaWorld, Aquatica, and Discovery Cove. Dolphins, whales, manatees, sea lions, and others perform.

name: Seminole Hard Rock Hotel and Casino
description: A very large hotel and event center, along with 2,000 slot machinces, restaurants, a beach club, and other gaming opportunities.

name: Shark Valley Tram Tours
description: This tour is in Everglades National Park 40 miles west of Miami. You can ride your own bike on the 15 mile long trail or take a tram tour.

name: Silver Springs State Park
description: The springs and attraction are in a Florida State Park. You can enjoy riding on the glass-bottomed boats, paddling in a kayak, or being amazed at the crystal-clear blue depths of Silver Springs.

name: Smallwood Store
description: This old store was opened in 1906 and is now operating as a museum that displays the items that were sold here to pioneers and Seminoles in the old days. It has survived six hurricanes (as of 2018).

name: Solomon's Castle
description: The late Howard Solomon was an artist who created art out of junk, including the castle-like museum. You will be amazed at his creations.

name: St. Augustine Alligator Farm
description: The oldest in Florida, and it features a huge selection of animals including gators and Maximo, the 14 foot long crocodile.

name: St. Johns Rivership Company
description: The 105 foot modern sternwheeler "Barbara Lee" takes you on a narrated cruise on the St Johns River from downtown Sanford.

name: Stephen Foster Folk Culture Center State Park
description: The park honors Stephen Foster, the composer of Florida's official song "Old Folks at Home". The museum here contains many exhibits and a carillon plays music during the day.
address: 11016 Lillian Saunders Dr (US-41), White Springs, FL 32096

name: Suncoast Primate Sanctuary
description: This is a non-profit foundation that is home to chimpanzees, orangutans, monkey, other primates, as well as birds.

name: Sunken Gardens
description: This botanical garden is more than 100 years old and includes 50,000 tropical plants and cascading waterfalls.

name: Tampa Museum of Science & Industry
description: Among its features are a planetarium. and several exhibits that explain science, health and wellness, space, and weather. They call it a scientific playground, and it has more than 100 hands-on activities.

name: Theatre Of The Sea
description: An old attraction where you can swim with dolphins and watch sharks, turtles, and other species swimming around in front of you.

name: The Ancient Spanish Monastery
description: This is the oldest building in Florida. Built in Spain in 1141, it was taken apart, and put back together in 1954.
address: 16711 West Dixie Hwy, North Miami Beach, FL 33160

name: The Dolphin Connection
description: This is one of the most popular places in the Florida Keys to learn about dolphins and swim with them.
address: Hawk's Cay Resort,61 Hawk's Cay Boulevard, Duck Key, FL 33050

name: The Florida Key Lime Pie Company
description: Great attraction next to Ron Jon Surf Shop with great desserts, gifts, and Sweetie the Alligator.

name: The Lightner Museum
description: In a former grand hotel, it has a large collection of fine and decorative 19th century art, much of it from the gilded age.

name: The Revs Institute
description: A formerly private collection, it's home to more than 100 beautiful autos manufactured between 1896 and 1995.

name: Tigertail Beach
description: A tranquil wild beach in the middle of busy Marco Island.

name: Truman Little White House
description: Florida's only presidential museum. The 33rd President of the U.S. stayed here many times and it displays some of his memorabilia.

name: Universal Orlando Resort
description: The second largest theme park in Orlando, it consists of two parks: Universal Studios Florida and Universal's Islands of Adventure. The Wizarding World of Harry Potter is a favorite attraction for the kids. There are also many individual resorts within Universal Studios.

name: University of Tampa (Tampa Bay Hotel)
description: The Henry B. Plant Museum is in the hotel and contains actual furnishings enjoyed by first guests to visit here.
address: Henry B Plant Museum, 401 West Kennedy Blvd, Tampa, FL 33606

name: Valiant Air Command Warbird Museum
description: This museum focuses on war planes from the earliest days of aviation to the present day. Their collection includes more than 45 historic warbirds.
address: Space Coast Regional Airport, 6600 Tico Road, Titusville, Florida 32780

name: Vizcaya Museum & Gardens
description: The Vizcaya Museum and Gardens is the former estate of James Deering of the Deering-McCormick International Harvester fortune.

name: Wakulla Springs State Park
description: The constant 70-degree waters are a wonderful retreat on hot summer days. You can also take a 45-minute riverboat tour where you will see alligators, manatee, and birds.
address: 465 Wakulla Park Drive, Wakulla Springs, FL 32327

name: Walt Disney World Resort
description: We cannot ignore the largest theme park in the world. People come here from all over the world;  affordability is a matter of opinion. The attractions here include the Magic Kingdom, Animal Kingdom, and more. You will also find more hotels in this area than any other location you can visit in Florida. Also has four championship golf courses.

name: Warm Mineral Springs
description: People come from all over the world to soak in the warm waters of this spring that supposedly has many healing minerals.
address: 12200 San Servando Ave, North Port, FL 34287

name: Webster Flea Markets
description: One of the largest flea markets in the world, this one if only open on Mondays. Thousands of vendors and anything you can think of.

name: Weeki Wachee Springs
description: An old attraction that features underwater mermaid shows and is now a state park with a water park attraction.

name: Wekiwa Springs State Park
description: This has been a popular recreational spot for Orlando area residents and tourists for more than 100 years. It is so popular that on many days from May through October they have to close it when the maximum capacity of 250 cars has been reached.

name: Wildlife Sanctuary of Northwest Florida
description: Your visit to this wildlife sanctuary will include seeing about 100 animals that cannot be released. This sanctuary provides care each year to more than 3,000 injured or orphaned wild animals native to Florida.

name: Winter Park Scenic Boat Tour
description: Several lakes in Winter Park are connected by scenic canals. The pontoon boat guides know their stuff and show you a lot of historical places and natural things on your one hour cruise.
address: 312 East Morse Blvd, Winter Park, FL 32789

name: Withlacoochee State Trail
description: The trail is a 46 mile long path on abandoned railroad tracks that follows a route roughly parallel to the Withlacoochee River. The path is paved and is a great location to hike, bike, and skate.

name: Wynwood Walls
description: The walls of the buildings in Wynwood are decorated by constantly changing murals by some of the world's most gifted and famous graffiti writers and street artists.

name: Ybor City Historic District
description: Known as Tampa's Latin Quarter for over a century, Ybor City is an exotic blend of aromas, flavors, sights and sounds.

name: Zoo Tampa at Lowry Park
description: The zoo is on 56 acres and includes many animal encounters. Park zones are dedicated to Asia, Africa, Australia, and Florida. More than 1,300 separate animals call it home.

name: Zoo World
description: The zoo specializes in conservation and has over 260 animals with numerous exhibits, programs, and performances in a tropical setting. This is an interactive attraction where you can do various thing with the animals.
address: 9008 Front Beach Road, Panama City Beach, Florida 32407
